<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Free Kids Typing Games on Kids Typing Games</title><link>https://localhost/</link><description>Recent content in Free Kids Typing Games on Kids Typing Games</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-gb</language><atom:link href="https://localhost/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>A–Z</title><link>https://localhost/games/az/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://localhost/games/az/</guid><description/></item><item><title>About</title><link>https://localhost/about/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://localhost/about/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Kids Free Typing Games is a collection of short, playful typing activities designed for very young learners (roughly ages &lt;strong&gt;2–6&lt;/strong&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="what-makes-it-different"&gt;What makes it different&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Free to play&lt;/strong&gt; — no sign‑ups required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Mobile friendly&lt;/strong&gt; — big targets, touch keyboard support, and short rounds.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Typing first&lt;/strong&gt; — letter practice, simple words, and confidence-building feedback.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Kid-safe vibes&lt;/strong&gt; — calm pacing, positive reinforcement, and clear instructions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id="tips-for-parents-and-teachers"&gt;Tips for parents and teachers&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Start with one game and keep sessions short (1–3 minutes).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Say the letter or word out loud first, then type together.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Celebrate effort, not speed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
